  "text": "Although the class of simplified vine distributions is extremely rich, the simplifying assumption may be grossly violated in some real-life data. Our second scenario, a Frank copula coupled with standard normal margins, violates this assumption (see Example 5.1 of [CITATION_1] . Again, we choose the parameter of the Frank copula such that all pair-wise Kendall's τ equal 0.4 (this corresponds to a Frank copula parameter θ ≈ 4.16). In this case, f vine is not consistent.",
